The man was injured in the surf at Umzumbe beach. Reports from the scene indicate that the man aged 75 was in the surf when he was hit by a freak wave. Paramedics arrived and found that the lifeguards and some members of the public [had] managed to pull the man from the surf and immobilise him on a trauma board said a statement by Netcare911. The Advanced Life Support paramedic from Netcare stabilised the patient before they transported him to a hospital in Port Shepstone for further care. The man was reported to have serious injuries.- TMG Digital